args: My first assignment after becoming a Paladyn\nwas to quell the civil war in the Belitz diocese.
The conflict began with the murder of a bishop,\nand the chaos quickly spread from there,\nSoon, laymen and clergy were at war.
In the end, countless residents who\nturned their backs on the Church\nwere put to death in Ilia's name.
O imperfect soul, be taken upon the flow\nof mana and go with the favor of the\ngoddess. May you find peace in her arms.
Have you finished your burials, Tobias?
This was the last. And having finished,\nI would ask you something.
Did we truly need to purge so many?
These people rejected Ilia's blessings\nand became heretics of their own will.\nTo a man, they got what they deserved.
By putting them to the sword, we prevent\ntheir souls from becoming even more\nsullied. In this way do we save them.
Now if you are finished, we need to\nbegin clearing away this rubble.
We ＂save＂ them? But how can— Ah!
Ho there! Who threw that stone?
Please don't harm my boy! I beg of you!
Don't defend him! He killed Daddy!
I've no intention of harming you\nor your child, good woman.
The battle is over. Any reason we\nmay have had to fight is gone.
Then why did you kill my husband?
The bishop was murdered and churches\nattacked. We did not start this conflict.
Yes you did! YOU were the ones\nwho started taking US away!
We were told the dragons\nrequired sacrifices.
You can play the fool all you like,\nbut that's exactly what your bishop told us.

We were told we had to make offerings to
the dragons, and to the development of the
Church. ...Offerings. Pah! Taxes are more
like it, for we'd little choice in the matter!

Then we were told our monetary sacrifices
were no longer enough, and that only by
offering our very lives to the dragons
could we hope to find salvation!
All we wanted was to live in peace,\nyet your Church took everything from us!\nWhy?! Why have you done this?!
You're nothing but a pack of murderers\nkilling in the name of a mad goddess!
*gasp* Heresy and slander! ...Come, men!\nTake this woman and clap her in irons!
Wait! We need to listen to—
She'll have all the time in the world to\nspeak once her inquisitor arrives.\nNow seize her AND her child!
The Church's members follow and worship\nIlia that they might find happiness.
And this—this...MADNESS—flies in the\nface of everything we hold dear!
Guide me, O Ilia! Show me the way!\nWhy does your Church even exist if\nthis is to be the result?!
...Then the cause of the civil war\nwas the Church's own barbarism?
Exactly. It was the end result of a faith that\nhad grown twisted.
When a faith has fallen so low as to claim\ninnocent lives, it is time for it to be left in\nthe past.
Then the reason you came down\non the side of the perditionists...
Yes. I thought perhaps lives could be\nspared if the Church were to change.

Even if that change caused bloodshed in
the initial phase, such sacrifices could
be justified if they served to usher in
a new era of wisdom and peace.

But our Church continued to rot from
within, becoming more malicious by the
day. That was when I knew even more
drastic measures would be required.
Is that what led you to attack the dragon?
Surely there must have been some\nother way to get what you wanted.
Righteous beliefs and heretical ones\nare two sides of the same coin.
I won't ask you to understand my beliefs.\nI just ask that you leave me alone.
There is only one way this will end:\nwith your charred corpse tied to a stake.\nIs that truly the result you desire?
Are you willing to die before achieving\nall you have set out to accomplish?
Only the heavens know who is truly right.\nIf my beliefs are heresy, it is only correct\nthat I am judged for them.
Also, I do not prize my own safety and\nwelfare over holding fast my convictions.\nThey are not so cheap as all that.
Enough. We have talked overlong.\nKindly leave me be.
(I now understand why he objects\nto the Church's current state.)
(But I ALSO understand he is thinking of\npeople's happiness as much as ever.)
O Ilia, pray lend me your wisdom.
What are righteous beliefs?\nWhat is heresy?
Two days remain until Tobias's trial...
